<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-40-0675 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book discusses the image processing technology in nuclear medicine.The techniques discussed are biomedical radiography, NMR imaging, ultrasonographyand computerized tomography as used for diagnostic purpose of skeletaldiseases; brain and spinal cord diseases; abdomen and gastrointestinaltract diseases; urinary and genital tract diseases and chest and facediseases. Infections diseases of chest and bone are described and specificallydescribed in ultrasonography of uterine diseases and evaluation of pregnancy.Congenital malformation of skeleton and hereditary diseases are alsodiscussed.</TEXT></DOC>